==English ==
===Etymology===
Variant of [[Amalia]] or [[Emilia}}
Derived from [[Germanic]] "amal" meaning "work".

===Namesake===
Amelia Earhart, the first woman to make a solo flight over the [[Atlantic Ocean]].

